plying a notional\nescape fraction. We compare our AGN LFs to predictions based on different\nblack-hole seeding models, finding decent agreement on average, but that all\nmodels are unable to predict the observed abundance of bright AGNs. We make\npredictions for the upcoming Euclid and Roman observatories, showing that their\nrespective wide-area surveys should be capable of discovering AGNs to z ~ 8.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 5 Jul 2022 18:00:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-10-26"}
