nterlayer coupling\n$J_{\\perp}$ of 10$^{-5}J$. Reflecting the 2D limit, an extended region of\nthermal fluctuations is observed from the BEC transition temperature $T_{\\rm\nc}$ up to $\\sim 2T_{\\rm c}$, which may carry certain BKT characteristics. At\n$H_{\\rm s}$, we clearly capture 2D-limit quantum fluctuations that can be\ndescribed as the formation of a highly mobile, interacting 2D Bose gas in the\ndilute limit.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 5 Jul 2022 21:46:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-07-07"}
